    <note>Huang(1) Shuao [856] Lian's [851] son, Tingjian's [7111] cousin, Li(2) Chang's [971] son-in-law. His grandson, Le [3417], was Liangzhe yunpan between 1209 and 1210 when he was appointed Taifu qing. Chao Buzhi, WJ, 66.1a (wife, surname Li(2), daughter of Chang, who married him at age 18 and died in 1093 at age 22); XNYL, 53.9a, 54.2b, 56.10a, 10b-11a, 60.7a, 9a, 62.1a, 64.7b, 13b, 67.9a, 69.5b, 77.10a; Xianchun Linan zhi, 50.10a; Guangdong TZ, 15.7a, 8a; SHY:ZG, 43.146a, 68.39a, 70.14b; SHY:SH, 53.2b. Information about the successive marriages to Li(2) Chang's [971] daughter and then to Chang's elder brother Xin's [13069] daughter can be found in Shuao's grandson's funerary inscription (Yuan Xie, WJ, 14.1b-2a). CBD, 4, 2900-1.</note>
